                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d525">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.12155/436: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morrow</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-07-09T12:00:00-06:00"
                            >July 9, 1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 6:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>140. Boundary Commissioner Lawson accompanied by Ainsworth and Moore arrived here
                    July 7.</p>
                <p>Lawson and Mexican Commissioner are preparing to complete final definitive report
                    of the rectification project. On completion the matter will be in the situation
                    where it can be incorporated into a treaty. I assume that Department desires me
                    to initiate negotiations as soon as the moment is propitious. I propose to
                    mention the matter to the President on Saturday when he receives me.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morrow</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
